{
  "stem": "3212.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But we had a terrible life because we had to go with the Star of David and we were recognized wherever we went.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And there were certain things we were allowed to do and certain things not.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "When we arrived in Theresienstadt, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we left the train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I don't know how many people-- thousands-- but there was no trucks or cars waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We had to walk from the train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Later on, the station was closer to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But when we arrived-- we arrived in October 1942-- we had to walk to the ghetto with SS, and Jewish guards on the side.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "There was-- in the ghetto was a Jewish Judenrat, they called it-- the Jewish community, elders-- that they ran the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They got orders from the Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But they ran actually the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We went through a registration place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And the ghetto, when we arrived, it looked terrible.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "It had big walls.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "It was a-- It was, in World War I, it was kazerne.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "It was a camp for military, for army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Brick walls all around.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was big, brick walls with deep, deep--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Trenches.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the ghetto by itself was all kazernes, different military headquarters.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they separated us right away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Me, I was separated from my parents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My brother was with my mother and father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the same thing happened to Walter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They separated-- Walter came with me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We went in a--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Walter is my cousin that-- from my uncle's son.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And since then, we went in a home of children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Walter and me, we went in one room.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was in a kazerne, but the whole-- the whole kazerne-- the whole building was with children.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
